<br>
----------------<br>
First, I wanna thank you all for making me remember what it is that I liked about EQ in the first place...<br>
<br>
A few weeks ago, I left my home in Rutabaga Paradox to join an &quot;Uber Guild&quot;. (I ain't saying which one, those of you who know me, already know which one)<br>
<br>
My reasons were:<br>
<br>
I wanna see places I haven't seen before.<br>
I wanna kill mobs I haven't killed before.<br>
<br>
Notice that the words &quot;phat&quot;, &quot;loot&quot;, &quot;lewts&quot;, &quot;leet&quot;, or any of the other words that children use to describe certain aspects of the high end game do not appear in the above list.<br>
<br>
Personally, I will consider myself DONE with EverQuest when I have travelled in every zone, and faced every mob that there is to face. I'm still a long way from that...<br>
<br>
I don't care about rotations.<br>
I don't care about &quot;skillz&quot; or any of that other crap.<br>
I don't care if I have the best item possible in each inventory slot.<br>
<br>
(I gotta admit, being the first on a server to kill something/accomplish something would be kinda nice. Like Sir Edmund Hillary or Lindbergh, being first is kinda cool, but hardly a priority.)<br>
<br>
What I *do* care about...<br>
<br>
Learning to play my character as well as I can.<br>
<br>
Having the reputation of a competent player who is a relatively nice guy and fun to hang out with.<br>
<br>
Experiencing as many new things as I possibly can in the game.<br>
<br>
Since I've &quot;gone to the darkside&quot;, I've been in ToV and killed just about everything in that zone. I've killed so many dragons, I've honestly lost count. I've seen a lot of mobs in Luclin that most folks have never heard of, and I've even managed to get an item that nobody else on the server has. (to my knowledge) So far, so good. Right?<br>
<br>
Well... I'll just say that whoever coined the phrase &quot;It's lonely at the top&quot; is a bloody moron.<br>
<br>
There are an awful lot of folks at the &quot;top&quot; of this server. Hoss, Vindication, ML, L`Malla, IG, NI, LMNOP... There are a lot of folks all trying to kill the same stuff. Hey, these guys all got together and settled on a rotation so that everyone would get a taste. Sounds fair to me. This is why rules are made. Give everyone a chance to enjoy their 10 bucks per month.<br>
<br>
Vindication decides that they system doesn't work for them, and they want out. Ok, that's their decision. They got the jump on L`Malla in ToV, happy killing. L`Malla will get over it in a little while and people will adjust to the idea of the server being Free For All.<br>
<br>
I'm not gonna answer the phone at 4:00 AM just because some mob spawned in BFE. I'm not gonna camp out near ANY mobs spawn point just to get a shot at it. EQ is a fun game, but frankly, my friends wouldn't understand me if I bragged about &quot;killing IV in AR&quot; or &quot;Clearing NToV in 8 hours&quot;. I'll still get to see new things, and kill new mobs. I'll still get what I want out of the game. <br>
<br>
Ultimately, nobody remembers the loot you've won, or the mobs you've killed, or the places you've been. They'll only remember one thing...<br>
<br>
&quot;Is this person a good guy? or a jerk?&quot;<br>
<br>
It's all you've got after you're done with EQ. It's your only legacy. Nobody cares who was first, or who had the most, or whatever... Just think about it the next time you post. Is the person reading your words rolling their eyes and thinking &quot;God, what an asshole!&quot; or do they sit back and smile and remember the time you &quot;got drunk and ran through Kelethin&quot;? Do they remember you as the guy who &quot;had phat lewtz?&quot; and bragged all the time? or the guy who ended a zone-wide argument by shouting &quot;I like skittles, my favorite ones are orange&quot;?<br>
<br>
Some of you are thinking...(sic)<br>
<br>
&quot;Screw them! Why do I care what anyone else thinks of me?&quot;<br>
<br>
Good point, but put down your punk rock records and look at the big picture for a moment. Are you really content with being NOTHING? Are you content with self congratulation? That's all you'll get. I've met quite a few people from EQ in real life. You know what the most frequently asked question is?<br>
<br>
a) &quot;What guild are you in?&quot;<br>
b) &quot;What loots do you have?&quot;<br>
c) &quot;What server are you on?&quot;<br>
d) &quot;What class do you play? What Level?&quot;<br>
<br>
Hint: A and B are almost NEVER asked. (nobody cares) and The answer to C and D provide about 30 seconds of conversation. <br>
<br>
More often than not, the MOST frequently asked question is something like...<br>
<br>
&quot;How bad did you get your ass kicked in &lt;insert common zone here&gt;?&quot;<br>
<br>
They want stories, humorous incidents, stupid things that everyone did when they learned the game. It's a common bond. You walk into a room of EQ players bragging about your &quot;Hammer of Uberness&quot; and most people will tune you out.<br>
<br>
THEY DON'T CARE!<br>
<br>
I must admit that I thought 95% of all of the &quot;Uber&quot; types were children who were obnoxious at best, utter buttheads at worst. I'm happy to say that the VAST majority of folks that I've met in the high end game are decent folks who just want to enjoy the results of all the hard work they put into their character. I've met some WONDERFUL folks in nearly EVERY guild. <br>
<br>
I remember sitting in OOT with members of Hoss trading stories about the STUPID things we did around level 20. <br>
<br>
I remember taunting some folks from Seekers and L`Malla when they accidentally trained me in Kaesora (&quot;Is that all you got? Don't worry guys, I'll clean up your messes.&quot;) and then sitting down with em later and having a laugh about it.<br>
<br>
I remember the first time I ever ran from Cobalt Scar to ToV to meet a friend of mine in ML.<br>
<br>
Hell, I've got a thousand other &quot;I remembers&quot;. That's the best part about the game. Not sitting in front of your computer parsing logs to figure out which Uber Weapon_01 does the most damage against Vulak.<br>
<br>
Finally, if you have a problem with the length or verbosity of my post, just remember...<br>
<br>
You read it all...<br>
<br>
